# Cloudflare Pages headers (https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/)
#
# Next.js `output: "export"` emits the dynamic OG/Twitter card routes as
# extensionless files (out/opengraph-image, out/twitter-image). Without a
# recognized extension, Cloudflare Pages serves them as application/octet-stream,
# so Slack / X / Facebook / LinkedIn / iMessage refuse to render the link
# preview. The files are valid PNGs — force the correct Content-Type.
/opengraph-image
  Content-Type: image/png
/twitter-image
  Content-Type: image/png
